maml:description.maml:para: Closes the window that launched the PowerShell runtime
Closes the window that launched the PowerShell runtime

maml:alert.maml:para: The command closes the Window that runs the script. This only applies to runners that e.g. is launched from Context Menu. If Close-Window is not executed before the end of script the Window that runs the script will remain visible, allowing user to e.g. see the text view of the results.
